I had a file where tabs were used for alignment (ewww I know) but when de-tabbing it would actually start to delete characters at the beginning of that line.

So use another editor to create a file containing something like this:

```
{
<tab>{
<tab><tab>First line which is OK
<tab><tab>Second<tab>line which is not
<tab>}
}
```

Open it in Atom IO, and then select all. Then hit Shift-Tab several times to remove all indentation, but keep hitting Shift-Tab even more.

It'll start to trim the second line! It'll keep trimming if you keep hitting Shift-Tab until it reaches the tab in the middle of the line.

I had lots of deeply nested code with completely wrong tabbing and I wanted to strip it all and go through it. Unfortunately, I ended up losing information due to this :-(

